'''''After Pearl''''' is a 1984 video game published by [[SUPERware]].

==Gameplay==
''After Pearl'' simulates naval warfare in the [[Pacific Theatre of World War II|Pacific theatre of World War II]].<ref name="CGW19" />

==Reception==
Bob DeWitt reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', stating "for those who are not dyed-in-the-wool wargamers, and who simply enjoy strategic planning and maneuvering without a lot of detail, this game may prove to be a mental exercise in the power of position."<ref name="CGW19">{{cite magazine |last=DeWitt |first=Bob |title=Micro-Reviews |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=December 1984 |volume=1 |issue=19 |pages=36â€“37}}</ref>

